{
  "texts": [
    "It focuses on challenging one's cognitive distortions and subsequent behaviors to reduce existing mental health symptoms and improve overall mental well-being [9,15].",
    "CBT is found to be effective in a variety of diagnoses, such as mood disorders, Attention-deficit/hyperactivity disorder (ADHD), eating disorders, Obsessive-compulsive disorder, and Post-traumatic stress disorder [26,31,34,36,40,73,95].",
    "CBT also shows promising results in preventative care that may not be tied to a specific diagnosis.",
    "It has been effective in various settings, including medical, work, and school environments [54,59,87].",
    "However, despite the abundant evidence of its effectiveness, CBT is associated with a high nonresponse rate, attributed to participants' low motivation [13]."
  ]
}